title: Thermosimfit
text: Using R package tsf specific parameters (kHD kGuest, I0, IHD ID) different algebraic systems can identified. preliminary work systems defined maxima (Information). Subsequently, two times specific variables eliminated yielding two polynoms. polynome contains known variables e.g. concentration host, variables optimized e.g. kGuest unknown variable either d hd. Afterwards, algebraic system loss function defined R. loss function receives arguments four parameter optimized returns error received parameter set. parameterset consists four parameters kHD kGuest, I0, IHD ID. Furthermore, constant parameters passed loss function e.g. concentration host data.frame contains independent variable (either dye guest) corresponding signal. using informations roots calculated polynome concentration independent variable. roots define corresponding concentration either d hd independent variable. Using roots silico signal calculated based following formula: \(Signal_{InSilico} = I_0 + I_{HD} [hd] + I_D [d]\) silico signal compared measured signal. better match smaller error returned loss function.

title: Thermosimfit
text: hg system: \[ \begin{align*} h + hd + -h0 = 0 \\ d + hd -d0 = 0 \\ hd / (h*d) -kd = 0 \\ \end{align*} \] ida gda system: \[ \begin{align*} h + hd + hga -h0 = 0 \\ d + hd -d0 = 0 \\ ga + hga -ga0 = 0 \\ hga / (h*ga) -kg = 0 \\ hd / (h*d) -kd = 0 \\ \end{align*} \]

code: opti(   case,   lowerBounds,   upperBounds,   path,   additionalParameters,   npop = 40,   ngen = 200,   Topology = "random",   errorThreshold = -Inf,   runAsShiny = FALSE )

title: Optimize algebraic systems which describe thermodynamic binding systems — opti
text: case character describing system investigated. Either: "hg", "ida" "gda". lowerBounds numeric vector defining lower boundaries parameter. case hg order parameters : khd, I0, IHD ID case ida ga order parameters : kg, I0, IHD ID. upperBounds numeric vector defining upper boundaries parameter. order lower boundaries. path filepath contains tabular x-y data. concentraion dye guest respectivly assumed first column. Furthermore, corresponding signal stored second column. alternative already loaded data.frame can passed function. additionalParameters required parameters specific case. case hg numeric vector length 1 expected contains concentration host. case ida numeric vector length 3 expected contains concentration host, dye khd parameter. case gda numeric vector length 3 expected contains concentration host, guest khd parameter. npop optional integer argument defining number particles optimization. default value set 40. ngen optional integer argument defining number generations particle swarm optimization. default value set 200. Topology optional character argument defining topology used particle swarm algorithm. options "star" "random". default topology "random" topology. errorThreshold optional numeric argument defining sufficient small error acts stop signal particle swarm algorithm. default value set -Inf. runAsShiny internally used running algorithm shiny.

title: Particle swarm optimization — pso
text: env something passed loss function addition parameters get optimized lb numeric vector defining lower boundaries parameter ub numeric vector defining upper boundaries parameter loss loss function optimal parameter set found ngen number generations pso run npop number particles used optimization error_threshold number defining sufficient small error optimization stopped global logical parameter. set TRUE global star topology used. Thus, particle compares global best particle entire swarm. contrast, global set FALSE random arbitrary neighborhood used instead. Thus, particle neighberhood contains K neighbours K 0 3. swarm K neighbours drawn randomly. neighberhood best particle used comparison. neighberhood calculated generation. saveSwarm logical value defining whether entire optimization saved. runAsShiny internal parameter used running shiny app interface.
